Risk assessment of use cases going live whitn the next 6 months THIS IS A** BETA version**, go/pipelineIQ These dashboards are here to cut through noise and help us nail Q4.** But if they’re missing the mark, we need to know fast, lease send your feedback through this 2 min [**feedback form](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeti8KXZGVaCy4EWoPUx0657vZKjWFFT2E1GjDi9FVvlOWknw/viewform?usp=header ) The Sales Execution Hub is an AI-driven, forward-looking workspace designed to help sales and field teams prioritize, course-correct, and accelerate execution at scale.At its core are prescriptive, actionable dashboards that give you both:A high-level view of pipeline health by region and territory (by SA FLM), andA granular lens into individual use cases — their qualification, risks, and acceleration potential.You can also interact with the data using Genie, your AI assistant (like ChatGPT), to ask questions in plain language and get instant, contextual insights — without digging through spreadsheets or dashboards manually.It’s built to cut through noise, surface where to lean in, and guide decisions that move the business forward — faster.

Got questions? We probably answered them already. Check [the FAQ](https://docs.google.com/document/d/12DJ0bdrMsXtfnU5ot_XmoYbkFRVkAK-VsBBqdVO7cTw/edit?usp=sharing) .Not answered. You need a walkthrough. Send me a note: luis.herrera@databricks.com

lines:
# Risk assessment Categories

 

 

✅ High — Bankable Pipeline
Use cases in Go are well-qualified, low-risk, and fully aligned with MEDDPICC. The champion, metrics, and decision path are clear — execution can proceed with confidence. These are your high-conviction commits: accelerate, remove friction, and replicate what works.

⚠️ Medium — Coachable Pipeline
Use cases in Fix & Go show strong potential but contain qualification gaps — perhaps the champion is weak, the value unproven, or the decision process unclear. Progress is possible, but only through targeted intervention. Leaders should coach, requalify, or rescope before more investment to bring these deals back on track.

🛑 Low — Forecast Noise
Use cases in Reset carry significant uncertainty or flawed assumptions. Missing metrics, absent champions, or unknown path to production signal that fundamentals need rebuilding. These aren’t lost use cases yet — they need rework to regain clarity before investing more Pause, requalify, or redirect effort to protect forecast integrity and team focus.

The table below provides a one-liner summary of each use case, along with an AI-generated confidence score assessing its health from a MEDDPICC perspective. It also includes a recommendation (walk/re-inspect, adapt/pivot, or proceed) and the top three drivers influencing the confidence level. You can obtain a more detailed tactical advice on any use case using [this Glean Agent](https://databricks.glean.com/chat/agents/e86cb3d6138a47d18a664e57d4af3c6d) go/uc-doctor-agent
Thanks Wesley Gentine and Toby Balfre for the feedback. The table below places Confidence and Risk Assessment at the center to make analysis easier. And less scrolling.

**Use cases going live the next 6 months that are likely to slip** You can check out any of the Glean agents below to dive in and get tailored advice based on your specific use case: go/uc-doctor-agent Diagnose UC health directly from Salesforce link to use case.
go/stakeholder-outreach-agent Build executive outreach plans tied to business priorities.
go/onboarding-review-agent Review onboarding plans to surface gaps, friction, and blockers.
go/value-soundbite-agent Turn technical work into crisp business-impact messages.
go/poc-review-agent Optimize PoC plans to deliver outcomes faster.
